# Cold Calling Playbook

Version: 1.0

Status: Approved

Purpose:

Provide a repeatable system for conducting outbound cold calls that consistently create conversations, qualify opportunities, and schedule discovery meetings without relying on scripts or personality.

---

# Objective

The purpose of a cold call is not to make a sale.

The purpose of a cold call is to begin a business conversation.

Success is measured by conversations created—not calls completed.

---

# Principles

- Every prospect is a business.
- Curiosity beats persuasion.
- Questions outperform pitches.
- Relevance creates attention.
- Respect earns trust.
- Consistency beats intensity.

---

# Preparation

Before making any call:

✓ Prospect Research completed

✓ CRM reviewed

✓ Decision maker identified

✓ Company website reviewed

✓ Recent news reviewed

✓ Industry understood

✓ Opportunity identified

✓ Previous contact history reviewed

Never make blind calls.

