# Call Flow

## Step 1

Introduction

State:

• Your name

• Company

• Reason for calling

Keep this under twenty seconds.

---

## Step 2

Permission

Ask if they have a minute.

Examples:

"Did I catch you at an okay time?"

"Do you have sixty seconds?"

Permission lowers resistance.

---

## Step 3

Reason

State one observation.

Examples:

"I noticed..."

"We've been helping businesses like yours..."

"I saw..."

Never begin with a generic sales pitch.

---

## Step 4

Discovery

Ask questions.

Examples:

How are you currently handling...

What has been your biggest challenge with...

Are you currently working on...

The prospect should speak more than you.

---

## Step 5

Qualification

Determine:

Need

Authority

Timeline

Budget (when appropriate)

Priority

Current provider

Urgency

---

## Step 6

Value

Explain how Global Concepts Media helps solve the identified problem.

Connect directly to the issue they described.

Never deliver a generic company presentation.

---

## Step 7

Next Step

Every successful call ends with one action.

Examples:

Discovery Meeting

Website Review

Growth Review

Proposal

Information Request

Referral

Follow-up Date

Never end without a defined next step.

---

# Handling Gatekeepers

Be respectful.

Never argue.

Never misrepresent your purpose.

Request assistance professionally.

Treat gatekeepers as allies.

---

# Voicemail Standard

Short.

Professional.

Simple.

Name

Company

Reason

Phone Number

One call to action.

Do not leave long sales messages.

---

# Follow-Up Standard

Immediately after every call:

Update CRM

Record notes

Assign outcome

Schedule follow-up

Create tasks

No call is complete until the CRM is updated.

